This week's deal is the second part of my continuing account of the recent ^*BIOC Grand Prix^*N in Salt Lake City. If you have not done so already, I suggest you read part 1 of this series, available as ^*BDeal of the Week 283^*N (February 11, 2002) through this web site. 

I am going to another tournament next week (the ^*BForbo^*N in The Netherlands) and I won't have time to do any work while I am away. I have therefore posted next week's ^*BDeal of the Week^*N (part 3 of this story) a week in advance. It is available now. Please read ^*BDeal of the Week 285^*N when you are finished with ^*BDeal of the Week 284^*N.

I hope you enjoy this week's deals!

^*BFred Gitelman^*N
^*BBridge Base Inc.^*N
^*Hwww.bridgebase.com^*N

Team Canada had upset the United States 23-7 in the first match of the 9-match round robin. My partner, Joey Silver, and I sat out the second match and we were happy to see that our teammates (^*BNick Gartaganis^*N-^*BPeter Jones^*N and ^*BKeith Balcombe-Gord Campbell^*N) scored up another 23-7 win, this time against India.

