Italy had passed us in the standings, but thanks to our excellent start, Canada was still in second place. The last match of the second day was a real test of character for our team. Joey and I were not really put to the test as we went to the bar instead of playing. The rest of the team faced the always dangerous Indonesians who were fighting hard for a qualifying spot. The other 4 members put a stop to our losing streak, getting a 16-14 Victory Point win against Indonesia.

Now 16-14 is not really a big win in terms of Victory Points, but it was a big win for our team. For one thing, beating Indonesia at all is an accomplishment. The fact that we were now supposed to be "feeling the pressure" and came through without our 2 most experienced players in the lineup was more important. The rest of the world was starting to learn that Canada was for real.

On the last day of the round robin we would play matches against Brazil, Poland, and Egypt. As long as our team was close to average in these 3 matches we would have a good chance to qualify (in the top 4) for the semi-finals. Were we feeling any pressure yet? It didn't seem like it. The guys on my team were playing and behaving like they had been here many times before!
